#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
stackmd_plus: build a single-file markdown "codebase pack" for LLM review,
with selected ai-digest-style features layered on top.

Preserved defaults from stackmd_portable:
- default output stays STACKMD-<FOLDER>-CODEBASE.md or STACKMD-<FOLDER>-DOCS.md
- positional directory still works
- manifest / reading guide / directory tree / file index remain central

Added features inspired by ai-digest:
- custom ignore patterns via .aidigestignore (configurable)
- custom minify patterns via .aidigestminify (configurable)
- whitespace removal is enabled by default, with --no-whitespace-removal to opt out
- --show-output-files [sort] to print included-file size stats with bars
- --watch to automatically rebuild on file changes
- --no-default-ignores to disable built-in ignore sets
- optional multi-input mode via -i/--input
"""

